  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Shelter, Settlements, and WASH Assistance for Populations Affected by the Northern Ethiopian Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In November 2020, tensions between the national and regional governments developed into widespread conflict in the Tigray Region of Ethiopia. The conflict has driven large-scale displacement, with populations fleeing to areas not directly under attack within the Tigray region, and to neighbouring Afar and Amhara Regions, and Sudan. The security situation in Tigray Region remains unstable, particularly in rural areas to which large numbers of people have fled, and access constraints due to persisting insecurity continue to challenge the urgent scale up of humanitarian assistance. This conflict, coupled with pre-existing humanitarian needs and against the backdrop of the COVID-19 pandemic in northern Ethiopia, has created a dire humanitarian situation, as numerous civilians have been displaced within Tigray, into other Ethiopian Regional States, and into neighbouring states such as Sudan. Through this project, IOM is contributing to the improvement of living conditions and the well-being of crisis-affected populations in Northern Ethiopia through Shelter and Settlements interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
